{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/the-heart-of-artificial-neural-networks-26627e8c03ba", "time": 1683001402.832483, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/the-heart-of-artificial-neural-networks-26627e8c03ba/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "The Math behind Artificial Neural Networks | by sampath kumar gajawada | Towards Data Science", "h1": "The Math behind Artificial Neural Networks", "description": "In this article, I will focus on the basic structure of the neuron, how a neuron works and the math behind neural networks. The inputs given to a perceptron are processed by Summation function and\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.analyticsvidhya.com/blog/2017/03/introduction-to-gradient-descent-algorithm-along-its-variants/", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 18}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sampath-kumar-gajawada/", "anchor_text": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sampath-kumar-gajawada/", "paragraph_index": 23}], "all_paragraphs": ["Just like the brain consists of billions of highly connected neurons, a basic operating unit in a neural network is a neuron-like node. It takes input from other nodes and sends output to others. \u2014 Fei-Fei Li", "Artificial Neural Networks have generated a lot of excitement in Machine Learning research and industry, thanks to many breakthrough results in speech recognition, computer vision and text processing.", "In this article, I will focus on the basic structure of the neuron, how a neuron works and the math behind neural networks.", "A simple artificial neuron having an input layer and output layer is called a perceptron.", "The inputs given to a perceptron are processed by Summation function and followed by activation function to get the desired output.", "This is a simple perceptron, but what if we have many inputs and huge data a single perceptron is not enough right?? We must keep on increasing the neurons. And here is the basic neural network having an input layer, hidden layer, output layer.", "We should always remember that a neural network has a single input layer, output layer but it can have multiple hidden layers. In the above fig, we can see the sample neural network with one input layer, two hidden layers, and one output layer.", "As a prerequisite for a neural network let us know what an activation function and types of activation function.", "The main purpose of the activation function is to convert the weighted sum of input signals of a neuron into the output signal. And this output signal is served as input to the next layer.", "Any activation function should be differentiable since we use a backpropagation mechanism to reduce the error and update the weights accordingly.", "So far, we learned the prerequisites that are a perceptron and activation function. Now let us dive into the working of neural network (the core of neural network).", "A neural network works based on two principles", "Let\u2019s understand these building blocks with the help of an example. Here I am considering a single input layer, hidden layer, output layer to make the understanding clear.", "We just randomly initialized the weights and continued the process. There are many techniques for initializing the weights. But, you may be having a doubt how these weights are getting updated right??? This will be answered using back propagation.", "Let us get back to our calculus basics and we will be using chain rule learned in our school days to update the weights.", "The chain rule provides us a technique for finding the derivative of composite functions, with the number of functions that make up the composition determining how many differentiation steps are necessary. For example, if a composite function f( x) is defined as", "Let us apply the chain rule to a single neuron,", "In neural networks, our main goal will be on reducing the error, to make it possible we have to update all the weights by doing backpropagation. We need to find a change in weights such that error should be minimum. To do so we calculate dE/dW1 and dE/dW2.", "Once you have calculated changes in weights concerning error our next step will be on updating the weights using gradient descent procedure. Please check more details on gradient descent here.", "Forward propagation and backward propagation will be continuous for all samples until the error reaches minimum value.", "Here we learned about the basics of what is a neuron, how neural network works. But, this is not enough there are many problems in updating the weights like neuron death, weights crossing the range, etc. I will be coming up with a new article having what are the challenges with activation functions and how to drop neurons to reduce the training error.", "Hope you enjoyed it !!! Stay tuned !!! Please do comment on any queries or suggestions !!!!", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Machine learning Enthusiast | Analyst | Programmer | All I write my own | Linkedin: https://www.linkedin.com/in/sampath-kumar-gajawada/"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F26627e8c03ba&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fthe-heart-of-artificial-neural-networks-26627e8c03ba&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fthe-heart-of-artificial-neural-networks-26627e8c03ba&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"ur